✔ CI/CD Integration (Expected in Lead Roles):
------------------------------------------------------------
Git triggers Jenkins build

Whenever code is pushed or PR is raised, Jenkins pipeline starts automatically.

Webhooks:
A webhook in Jenkins is a mechanism that automatically triggers a Jenkins job
when something changes in your Git repository
GitHub → Jenkins communication.

PR Build Pipelines:
Before merging
Tests run
Linting runs: code level errors
Selenium/Appium suite runs
Coverage reports generated
If build fails → PR cannot be merged.
This ensures code quality before release.
Git triggers Jenkins build:

================================================================================================
installing and working with git:
check git version:
git --version

Setup your global username and email once:
git config --global user.name "ShantappaBajare"
git config --global user.email "shantappabajare@gmail.com"

Check settings:
git config --list

Create a folder for your projects:
mkdir C:\GitRepos
cd C:\GitRepos

Create your first local repository:
mkdir demo-project
cd demo-project
git init

Create a file:
echo "print('Hello World')" > app.py

Add file to staging area:
git add app.py

Commit the file:
git commit -m "Initial commit"

#Now Git is fully working locally

---------------------------------------------------------------------------

Step to Connect With GitHub:
-----------------------------
Create a repository on GitHub
Do not add README/ .gitignore for first time (optional but simple).

https://github.com

If you don’t have an account → click Sign up and create one.
If you already have an account → Log in.

git remote add origin https://github.com/ShantappaBajare/demo-project.git
git branch -M main
git push -u origin main





